 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      Ten years have passed  since  Nathan  "RAD"  Spencer,  the      ｱｱｱｱ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      Bionic Commando,  managed  to  defeat  the  Imperials  and      ｲｲｲｲ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      destroy their secret weapon, the Albatross, in the  events      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      of Bionic Commando Rearmed. In the aftermath, Spencer  and      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      his comrade Joseph  "Super Joe"  Gibson  were  praised  as      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      heroes by the entire nation.                                    ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      TASC, the military intelligence organization that provided      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      Spencer with his Bionic  Arm,  soon  found  their  bionics      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      program in great demand. Now under the command  of  Joseph      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      Gibson,  the  organization  flourished,  and  many   other      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      operatives were enhanced with bionic parts.                     ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      As the original Bionic  Commando,  Nathan  Spencer  became      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      responsible for training these new operatives. At the same      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      time, Spencer began to undertake a series  of  high  risk,      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      covert  operations.  On  one   such   mission,   codenamed      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      Operation Blackout (the events of which  are  detailed  in      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      the comic book  Chain  of  Command),  Spencer痴  sense  of      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      justice came  into  conflict  with  the  orders  from  his      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      superior and friend Gibson.                                     ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      In refusing to kill two rogue bionic  prototypes,  Spencer      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      disobeyed a direct  order  which  ultimately  led  to  the      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      deaths  of  several  TASC  agents.  Spencer   was   court-      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      martialed, convicted of treason, and sentenced to death.        ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      As Spencer rotted on death row, his conviction changed the      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      public's view on bionic technology, and  opinions  on  the      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      subject became  divided.  Pro-  and  anti-bionic  factions      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      arose out of this dissension, and what started as a debate      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      over morals descended into civil unrest.                        ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      The issue came to a head when a Presidential directive was      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      issued to shut down the controversial bionics program.  In      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      what came to  be  known  as  the  "Bionic  Purge",  TASC's      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      bionics program was closed, and TASC personnel with bionic      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      augmentations were ordered to turn  in  their  bionics  or      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      have them forcibly removed. But this  heavy-handed  tactic      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      backfired, as pro-bionic followers  rioted,  and  many  of      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      TASC's bionic operatives chose to flee instead  of  giving      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      up their artificial parts.                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ                                                                      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      The chaos eventually subsided, and the  bionic  technology      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      was purged from  the  nation.  Pro-bionic  followers  went      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛﾛ      underground, and the nation once again knew  peace.  Until      ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
 ﾛﾛﾛｲ      today...                                                        ﾛﾛﾛﾛ
